This paper proposes a methodology for training compact and efficient LSTM models for language modeling and speech recognition applications. The paper focuses on leveraging hardware-impacted hysteresis effect and sparsity to achieve the symbiosis of model compactness and accuracy with execution efficiency. This work involves machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV).
